Movie: Motion Picture (Employees Leaving the Lumière Factory)

Review: I have put off watching this for years and I'm glad I did. I am much further in the process of untangling my own religion now than I was just a couple years ago. This raised so many questions and thoughts in me that are impossible to unpack in this small text, but here goes.To me, growing up christian was hell. But I didn't manage to speak up about it and leave church(basically a cult) before I turned 18.…

Movie: I Am Not an Easy Man

Review: Honestly one of the biggest surprises of the year so far for me. Went in with low expectations because of the mixed reviews, but I thought it was great. Yes, it is silly and stupid. But in a good way and regardless of what the intention was.
Five layers of jackets, but still cold. Tooth aches and broken cars plowing snow. No heat, no hope.

Movie: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Mutant Mayhem

Review: Love it when a movie is set in a part of the world I was not really aware of. Seeing the big and little things that make life a little different there. In this case, Yanbian. A cold and icy province of China bordering to North Korea.
This time of year it feels like I'm the only letterboxd user that is not a horror nut. So rewatching this is my little silent protest to the craze (I really dont get it).

I watched Brewster McCloud just before this. The climax of both films is a little wimpy boy with glasses, strapped with white wings, taking flight and gracefully flying for some time before crashing face first into the ground. Did not plan that, what a coinsidence.

Movie: Édouard Glissant: One World in Relation
Alone in the Woods: The Legend of Cambo
The Wonderful Story of Henry Sugar

Review: At one point I wanted an insufferable, babbling drunk man to just get smacked in the face by a woman so badly. So yeah, another banger from Mr. Hong Sang Soo.

Movie: It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown
Good Luck to You, Leo Grande

Review: Watching this at 7am was a great start to my day. Who needs coffee when you have epic kaiju fights to wake you up in the morning. Love the "matter of factness" of the whole thing from the script, world building, bureaucracy and even to the effects which are crazy, but also minimalistic at the same time.

Movie: Giant God Warrior Appears in Tokyo

Review: So interesting to see how similar but also different Johns earlier work is. Didn't know he had this style even before the hbo show. Hope to see more in the future, his insight is truly unique and valuable.
